	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Search and open your Firefox bookmarks from Alfred.

Usage
-----

- Hotkey — open bookmark search instantly (set your shortcut in the workflow editor)
- `bm [query]` — Show bookmarks filtered by query
  + `↩` — Open in app_default
  + `⌘+↩` — Open in app_cmd
  + `⌥+↩` — Open in app_alt
  + `^+↩` — Open in app_ctrl
  + `⇧+↩` — Open in app_shift
  + `fn+↩` — Open in app_fn
- `bmsettings` — Edit settings.json (configure Firefox profile path and apps)
- `bmupdate` — Force a refresh of the bookmark cache
- `bmhelp` — Open the help file in your browser

Configuration
-------------

Run `bmsettings` to open settings.json.

  firefox_profile  — Path to your Firefox profile directory (null = auto-detect)
  app_default      — App opened with ↩ (e.g. "Firefox", "Safari", "Browser")
  app_cmd          — App opened with ⌘+↩
  app_alt          — App opened with ⌥+↩
  app_ctrl         — App opened with ^+↩
  app_shift        — App opened with ⇧+↩
  app_fn           — App opened with fn+↩

Use "Browser" as the app name to open in the system default browser.
Any app_* value may be a list to open in multiple apps simultaneously.</string>
